The paper deals with the fundamental limits of a cache-aided wireless network from a latency-centric perspective, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), and system optimization (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of beamforming and multicasting, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
